
[1]pleasant

   PLEASANT, a. plez'ant.

   1. Pleasing; agreeable; grateful to the mind or to the senses; as a
   pleasant ride; a pleasant voyage; a pleasant view. Light is pleasant to
   the eye; an orange is pleasant to the taste; harmony is pleasant to the
   ear; a rose is pleasant to the smell.

   How good and how pleasant it is for brethren to dwell together in
   unity! Ps.133.

   2. Cheerful; enlivening; as pleasant society or company.

   3. Gay; lively; humorous; sportive; as a pleasant companion.

   4. Trifling; adapted rather to mirth than use.

   5. Giving pleasure; gratifying.

   This word expresses less than delightful, to the mind, and delicious,
   to the taste.
